From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
Date: 2026-05-27
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: declare softdep on af_xdp_pool so it autoloads with the netdev

Spec section 3.3 (dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md v4.4) prescribes
MODULE_SOFTDEP("pre: af_xdp_pool") on dpaa_eth.ko so that any module
autoload that pulls in fsl_dpaa_eth (uevent for the FMan platform
device, "ip link set fm1-mac3 up", systemd network bring-up) also
pulls in af_xdp_pool.ko before dpaa_eth.ko's register_netdev() runs.

Without this softdep, the observed behaviour on the deployed v4.4 ISO
(2026.05.27-0151-rolling, kernel 6.18.33-vyos) is:

  1. fsl_dpaa_eth.ko is autoloaded by the FMan platform-device uevent
     at boot.  af_xdp_pool.ko is NOT autoloaded - nothing in modules.dep
     or modules.alias references it.
  2. dpaa_eth_probe() calls register_netdev() with priv->qmgmt_ops==NULL
     (no flavor module registered yet).  net_dev->xdp_features therefore
     lacks NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY.
  3. Userspace bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) on the netdev fails at the XSK core
     layer with -EOPNOTSUPP (95), before any DPAA1 code runs, because
     xdp_features doesn't advertise the capability.
  4. An operator who knows the answer does `modprobe af_xdp_pool` once.
     af_xdp_pool_init() calls dpaa_register_flavor_ops(), the
     0069a-dpaa-flavor-ops-retro-attach.patch retro-attach path walks
     every existing dpaa_priv and republishes xdp_features with
     NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY set, and subsequent binds succeed.

That "do modprobe once per boot" step is the gap.  Three options were
considered:

  (a) CONFIG_DPAA_AF_XDP_POOL=m -> =y in 08-dpaa1.config.
      Forces the flavor module into the kernel image.  Costs ~few KB
      of kernel text on every flavor (default, vpp, ask) regardless of
      whether AF_XDP zero-copy is ever used.  Hardest to revert.

  (b) /etc/modules-load.d/dpaa-af-xdp-pool.conf via a chroot hook.
      ISO-only fix.  Doesn't help anyone running this kernel patch
      series on a stock distro without the VyOS image.  Bypasses the
      kernel-side fix.

  (c) MODULE_SOFTDEP("pre: af_xdp_pool") in dpaa_eth.c.  This patch.
      In-tree fix.  modprobe(8) honours softdep via depmod-generated
      modules.softdep; the chain "load fsl_dpaa_eth" -> "first
      pre-load af_xdp_pool" is enforced wherever modprobe is the
      loader.  Empty cost for !DPAA setups (the softdep is only
      consulted if dpaa_eth is being loaded).  Reversible by removing
      one line.  Upstreamable.

We pick (c).  Precedent: lib/libcrc32c.c carries
MODULE_SOFTDEP("pre: crc32c") for the same reason (consumer wants the
provider loaded first, but the provider isn't a hard link-time
dependency).

Effect after this patch:

  - depmod produces a modules.softdep line:
        softdep fsl_dpaa_eth pre: af_xdp_pool
  - The uevent autoload of fsl_dpaa_eth now first triggers
    `modprobe af_xdp_pool` (via kmod_module_probe_insert_module's
    softdep walker), which runs af_xdp_pool_init() and registers
    qmgmt_ops BEFORE dpaa_eth_probe() runs register_netdev().
  - dpaa_eth_probe() sees qmgmt_ops != NULL, sets
    NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY in net_dev->xdp_features in the
    initial publish, and the post-up bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) probe
    succeeds without the manual modprobe step.

Verification on the next ISO build:

  1. lsmod shortly after boot must show af_xdp_pool present BEFORE
     any user runs modprobe.  Check via
        sudo systemd-analyze critical-chain network-online.target
     plus `journalctl -k | grep -E 'af_xdp_pool|fsl_dpaa_eth' | head`.
  2. ip -d link show eth4 | grep xdp-features must include
     'xsk-zerocopy' (or equivalent, depending on iproute2 version)
     immediately after boot, BEFORE any manual modprobe.
  3. bin/dpaa1-xsk-bind-probe.py eth4 0 4096 must return rc=0 on a
     freshly booted system with NO `modprobe af_xdp_pool` step.

Backwards compatibility: a kernel without af_xdp_pool.ko available
(e.g. CONFIG_DPAA_AF_XDP_POOL is not set) sees the softdep, fails to
find the module, logs a warning via modprobe, and continues loading
dpaa_eth.  Same end-state as today: dpaa_eth runs without flavor ops
and netdev comes up without NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY.  No
regression for !DPAA-AF_XDP setups.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index 1111111111aa..1111111111bb 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -3,3 +3,4 @@ module_exit(dpaa_unload);
 
 MODULE_LICENSE("Dual BSD/GPL");
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("FSL DPAA Ethernet driver");
+MODULE_SOFTDEP("pre: af_xdp_pool");
